Lecture 2



Document Object Model

tree of element/nodes created by the browser.

The DOM model represents a document with a logical tree. Each branch of the tree ends in a node, and each node contains objects. DOM methods allow programmatic access to the tree; with them you can change the document's structure, style or content. Nodes can have event handlers attached to them. Once an event is triggered, the event handlers get executed.

console.dir(document) //all the dom elements

Selector
There are three diferent way to query the DOM

1. getElementById();

innerText: pays attention to the styling
textContent: doesn't pay attention to the styling

<p> hello <span style="displaye:none">  123 </span></p>

innerText: will display hello 
textContent: will display 123

